# Grade-by-Subject Descriptive Statistics and Regression Results\par
\par
JMTES is coded as the treatment school and JES as the comparison school. Scores are pooled across available ATLAS waves within each grade-subject cell. The difference in means is JMTES minus JES; positive values indicate higher average scores at JMTES.\par
\par
Note: the Word-compatible `.doc` report is stored as text-based RTF content so it can be reviewed in environments that do not support binary Word diffs.\par
\par
